in science; the nature and role of fictions in science; and the relationship between simulation and experiment, theories and data, and theories at different levels of description. Science in the Age of Computer Simulation will transform many of the core issues in philosophy of science, as well as our basic understanding of the role of the digital computer in the sciences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 0aSciencexData processingxPhilosophy. 0aSciencexExperimentsxComputer simulation. 0aSciencexMethodology. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  acomputer simulation, economics, ecology, engineering, climate science, high-energy physics, astrophysics, experimentation, analysis, scientific method, evidence, values, ethics, theories, data, methodology, nonfiction, models, uncertainty, truth, research, astronomy, weather, global warming, stem, conservation, preservation, technology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226902050423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226902050/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles